I did not do any wire scanning/matching on my shifts. RF kick data - DONE. title: * Re: Changed XTCAV OTRDMPB BPM offset from +11 mm to +13 mm
text: It looks like it was being watched while the cavity was still ramping up. Known oddity with XTCAVB: the actual cavity phase seen by the beam lags behind while the amplitude is shifting. Much more than XTCAV(H). Could not solve the problem using gain alone. Once it reaches full amplitude it stabilizes to the desired orbit. Here, the orbit was actually lagging behind at 9.5 mm during the ramp while set for 11 mm. Turning up the orbit set point to 13 mm happened around the same time the amplitude was just stabilizing, and converged back on the screen. But, setting the target that high can cause frequent amplitude cycles as some shots jitter outside the trip envelope. So: It may be better to stick with 11-11.5 mm and simply wait for the amplitude to stabilize from a ramp. See if beam is then on the screen. Meanwhile, I'm pinging the cavity experts again to understand the very slow phase/amplitude slew.
